<BODY>
<HEADLINE> India Cuts Custom Duty </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
According to an official press release issued here Friday,
custom duty on items like electronic toy and video games
components would be reduced from the peak level of 35 percent to
five percent.
</P>
<P>
On security systems, the duty was reduced from 35 percent to 15
percent while papers and their parts were cut from 25 percent to
five percent, and optical fiber cables from 35 percent to 25
percent.
</P>
<P>
Customs duty on electronic calculators has been brought down
from 20 percent to five percent.
</P>
<P>
The duty reduction and the raising of excise duty exemption
limit was effective from Friday, the press release said.
</P>
<P>
Earlier, India liberalized foreign direct investment (FDI) to
facilitate 100 percent foreign investment in certain
telecommunication areas as well as Special Economic Zones (SEZ) in
the country.
</P>
<P>
Briefing reporters about the government decision after a
cabinet meeting, an official spokesman said that India would also
allow oversees venture capital funds to invest in domestic
ventures subject approval by the Security and Exchange Board of
India (SEBI).
</P>
</TEXT>
