<HEADLINE> Xinhua Mideast News Summary at 2010 GMT, September 2 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA -- Turkish authorities were preparing strict inspection
of bilge waters released from ships transiting Bosporus and
Dardanelles Straits linking the Black Sea and the mediterranean
Sea, Turkish Daily News reported on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The initiative was taken jointly by the Istanbul Directorate for
Environment and the Borders and Coastlines Health Directorate,
aiming at curbing the increasing pollution in the Marmara Sea.
(Turkey-Environment)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
ANKARA -- The Turkish military will move its naval headquarters
from Golcuk in the Marmara region to Izmir on the Aegean Sea,
reported Turkish Daily News on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The decision was made in view of the devastating earthquake,
which hit the Marmara region on August 17, 1999. Golcuk was among
the cities suffering the heaviest damages in the quake that killed
17,000 people.  According to the decision, the Navy's main base
will also be moved from Golcuk to Aksaz of Marmaris, Mugla
province, on the Aegean Sea. (Turkey-Navy)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY -- Qatar has offered written proposals aimed at
ending the sufferings of the Iraqi people who have reeled under the
10-year-long U.N. sanctions.
</P>
<P>
The proposals were put forward during a meeting of the Gulf
foreign ministers, reports reaching here said Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The foreign ministers of the Gulf Cooperation Council (GCC)
states decided to study the ideals, said a final communique issued
at the end of the two-day meeting held in the western Saudi city
ofJeddah. (Qatar-Iraq-Sanctions)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
CAIRO -- Egyptian Foreign Minister Amr Moussa said on Saturday
that it is unlikely that the Palestinians and Israel will be able
to reach a final peace agreement by the endof 2000.
</P>
<P>
Moussa told the Egyptian television that the Palestinians and
Israel will need as long as one year to negotiate the details of
the final peace accord after a framework agreement on the main
issues of the conflict is reached.
</P>
<P>
If the two sides are able to reach an agreement in the next
three months, before United States President Bill Clinton leaves
office, it will not be a "detailed, full and comprehensive
agreement," he said. (Egypt-Mideast Peace-Accord) 
</P>
</TEXT>
