<HEADLINE> Japan Pounds Kuwait 6-0 at Friendly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, September 2 (Xinhua) -- Japan stormed to a 6-0 rout over
Kuwait with a second-half scoring spree in a friendly match at
Osaka on Saturday in preparation for the upcoming Olympics Games.
</P>
<P>
But the host failed to convert their dominance into scoring
until two minutes into the second half.
</P>
<P>
Shunsuke Nakamura broke the ice after slotting home a pass from
AS Roma midfielder Hidetoshi Nakata.
</P>
<P>
Since then Nakata failed to shine again as he wasted a penalty
in the 50th minute and hit another shot over the bar in the 60th
minute before leaving the pitch.
</P>
<P>
Nakamura stole spotlight from Nakata by setting for Kota
Yoshihara's two goals in the 74th and 85th minutes while scoring
another in a 83rd-minute penalty.
</P>
<P>
Junichi Inamoto and Tomoyuki Hirase were also on scoring sheet
with goals in the 76th and 89th minutes.
</P>
<P>
Kuwait tried to reply but luck was not on their side as Bashar
Abdulaziz's shot went wide in the 36th minute while Abdulaziz's
55th-minute goal was called "off side."
</P>
<P>
Japan will take on Morocco on Tuesday in Tokyo before leaving
for Canberra and Brisbane where they take on South Africa,
Slovakia and Brazil in Group D.
</P>
<P>
Kuwait will play the United States, the Czech Republic and
Cameroon in Group C. 
</P>
