<HEADLINE> China's First Navy Square </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DALIAN, September 2 (Xinhua) -- A ceremony was held in this
port city in northeast China's Liaoning Province today to
inaugurate the country's first Navy Square.
</P>
<P>
The square is the third of its kind in the world, after the
ones in Britain and the United States. It covers 69,000 square
meters and is decorated with over 280 trees of rare species, a
music fountain, sculptures of sailors and soldiers, and a 70-meter-
long naval ship.
</P>
<P>
Located at the southernmost tip of Liaodong Peninsula, Dalian
is the largest port city in northeast China and an important naval
base of the country.  
</P>
