<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Singapore Landing Ship Accomplishes Round-the-World Voyage </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, September 2 (Xinhua)-- The Republic of Singapore
Navy's (RSN) Landing Ship Tank, RSS Endurance returned home
Saturday after a four-month round-the-world voyage, making it the
first RSN ship to circumnavigate the globe and to pass through
both the Suez and Panama Canals.
</P>
<P>
RSN Chief Lui Tuck Yew as well as families and friends of the
crew of RSS Endurance went gathered at the Tuas Naval Base off the
southwestern coast of the island to welcome the ship home.
</P>
<P>
Singapore Ministry of Defense (MinDef) said in a press release
that RSS Endurance, which set sail from its home port on May 5,
2000, took the voyage with the objective of "Making Waves, Forging
Global Friendship" and called at nine ports -- Honolulu of the U.S.
, Acapulco of Mexico, Norfolk and New York of the U.S., Halifax of
Canada, Plymouth of the United Kingdom, Toulon of France,
Alexandria of Egypt and Jeddah of Saudi Arabia.
</P>
<P>
As part of the voyage, the crew took the opportunity to conduct
exercises and drills with navies of some host countries visited
and the Landing Ship Tank participated in the U.S. Navy
International Naval Review 2000 held in conjunction with the U.S.
Independence Day on July 4, 2000, MinDef said.
</P>
<P>
Officers and men from RSS Endurance also made courtesy calls to
naval commanders and officials at each port of call and hosted
visiting dignitaries and personnel from various military services,
MinDef added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
