<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Int'l Cliff Painting Symposium Opens </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YINCHUAN, September 2 (Xinhua) -- The 2nd Ningxia International
Cliff Painting Symposium opened in this capital city of northwest
China's Ningxia Hui Autonomous Region today.
</P>
<P>
More than 130 sculptors and experts from 13 countries attended
today's opening ceremony.
</P>
<P>
Cliff paining, as one of the most popular form of arts in the
world, has been discovered in over 120 countries. China has found
thousands of cliff paintings in over 20 provinces.
</P>
<P>
Helan Mountain alone, once a nomadic area, is the home to
thousands of cliff paintings carved by nomads in northern China
some 2,000 years ago. They are scattered over an area stretching
several hundred of kilometers.
</P>
<P>
During the five-day symposium, participants will put emphasis
on cliff painting and modern art, protection of cliff paintings
and the discovery of cliff paintings at Helan Mountain. They
agreed to build a museum to display cliff paintings from various
parts of the world at Helan Mountain.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
