<HEADLINE> China Leather Forum Held in East China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, September 2 (Xinhua) -- More than 100 Chinese and
overseas scholars and entrepreneurs attended the one-day China
Leather Development Forum, which was held in Haining in east China
's Zhejiang Province today.
</P>
<P>
The participants concentrated on the opportunities and
challenges for leather development in the 21st century and sought
new ways for leather development.
</P>
<P>
Zhang Shuhua, an official with the China Association of Leather
Industry, said that China is a large leather goods producer in the
world. However, it lags behind other countries in terms of name
brand quality and export price. He said his country must shift
from the previous trend of paying too much attention to quantity
to a trend of paying more attention to quality.
</P>
<P>
China plans to develop three to five internationally renowned
brands in the next 10 to 15 years, cultivate key genuine leather
manufacturers and reduce the amount of pollution caused by leather
enterprises, he added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
