</P>
<P>
-- President Clinton's decision to put off work on a missile
shield comes just days before he is to meet world leaders in New
York. He has taken off the table an issue that might have soured
his scheduled meeting with other leaders of Russia, China and U.S.
closest allies in Europe, who voiced fears that the constructions
of the system could violate the ABM Treaty and trigger a new arms
race.
</P>
<P>
-- The presidents of South America's 12 nations, in a statement
issued at the summit meeting in Brasilia, rebuffed President
Clinton's recent appeal that they endorse an American-backed
military and police offensive against drug trafficking and
guerrilla groups in Colombia. 
