<HEADLINE> Swedish Rally Kills Two Spectators </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
STOCKHOLM, September 2 (Xinhua) -- Tragedy in auto racing
happened again as two spectators were killed by a competing car
during a Swedish championship rally at Sandviken on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
According to local reports, the car went off the road coming
into a right turn about 200 meters (yards) after the start of a
special stage at Berga.
</P>
<P>
The rally was stopped immediately by the organizers and will
not be resumed.
</P>
<P>
Two Swedish rally drivers were killed during local rallies in
1998 and 1992 respectively. In 1982, two spectators were seriously
injured when hit by a car in another Swedish rally. 
</P>
</TEXT>
