<HEADLINE> Thailand to be Air Transport Carriers' Distribution Center </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, September 2 (Xinhua) -- Three key air transport
carriers in the world have eyed Thailand to be their center for
distribution of air mails and parcels to the region, according to
the Thai News Agency Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Deputy Director-General of the Customs Department Rapee
Asumpinpong was quoted as saying that Thailand has comparative
advantage of geographical location, so three major air transport
carriers -- Fed-Ex, DHL and UPS are planning to use it as their
hub for distribution in the Indo-Chinese region countries,
including Cambodia, Laos, and Vietnam as well as Malaysia,
Singapore, and Southern part of China.
</P>
<P>
The major carriers have begun to use their own air freighters
to deliver, rather than using the service provided by air liners.
</P>
<P>
Thailand's Second Bangkok International Airport, known as Nong
Ngoo Hao Airport, which is scheduled to be officially open in
years, can well facilitate the plan, Rapee said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
