last year while its exports to Malaysia was about 9 billion U.S.
dollars.
</P>
<P>
U.S. investments in Malaysia have grown more than 300 percent
since 1990 and stood at 5.9 billion U.S. dollars at the end of
last year with most U.S. investments concentrated in the
manufacturing sector, particularly in electronics and components.
