<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Zimbabwe Determined to Turn Economy Around </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, September 2 (Xinhua) --The Zimbabwean government is
determined to turn around the economy and uphold the already
peaceful and stable environment for the good of the country, vice-
president Joseph Msika said Friday.
</P>
<P>
Opening the annual Harare Agricultural Show, he said the
magnificent exhibits and products on display were an indication of
the country's ability to pull through the current hardships,
contrary to predictions often made by adversaries.
</P>
<P>
The agricultural sector, agricultural machinery and the
manufacturing sectors all illustrate the robust industrial base of
Zimbabwe," he said.
</P>
<P>
It is generally expected that before the economy stabilizes it
has to go through some ups and downs.
</P>
<P>
He said the small-scale and communal farmers are major players
in the economy as seen by their participation at the show.
</P>
<P>
Through our land reform program, this sector will grow in size
and will produce more crops and livestock products," he said.
</P>
<P>
The vice-president said that farmers had encountered problems
they never experienced before because of the enormous difficulties
besetting the country.
</P>
<P>
He urged the commercial, industrial, mining and informal
sectors, the civil society, the government and the agricultural
sector to work together for the prosperity of the country. End
item
</P>
</TEXT>
