<HEADLINE> Eight Companies Bid for Mobile Phone Licenses in Macao </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, September 2 (Xinhua) -- Eight companies in Macao, Hong
Kong and Singapore have submitted application forms to compete for
new licenses for mobile phone business in Macao, the Macao Daily
News reported Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The competition is a key move to open the local
telecommunications market. Government officials said the
application is encouraging and it shows that mobile phone services
attract investors very much.
</P>
<P>
The telecommunications authorities will examine the
applications and issue licenses to qualified competitors in mid-
October. Official sources said three licenses may be issued at
most.
</P>
<P>
At the end of June this year, there were 140,000 mobile phone
users in Macao with a population of 430,000. At present, the Macao
Telecommunications Company (CTM) dominates local mobile phone
services.  
