<HEADLINE> Chinese Cultural Expo to Debut in New York City </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHICAGO, September 1 (Xinhua) -- A Close Look at China -- a
free cultural celebration will make its U.S. debut in New York
City at the Jacob K. Javits Convention Center from September 6
through September 15, said an official news release issued Friday.
</P>
<P>
Sponsored by China's Information Office of the State Council
and the Ministry of Culture, the exhibition will offer an
unprecedented chance for Americans to look at the beauty and
diversity of Chinese culture.
</P>
<P>
The exhibit will feature Chinese fashion, art and tourism. Top
Chinese models in traditional costumes and the latest fashion by
the best Chinese designers, will perform as part of a spectacular
display of 2000 years of Chinese fashion history.
</P>
<P>
The event will showcase a 300-piece collection of rare Chinese
art and sculpture from master craftsmen and contemporary artisans,
including carved jadeware, stone and wooden sculptures, pottery,
porcelain and metal work.
</P>
<P>
A stunning travel exhibit that takes visitors on "A Journey
Through China" will explore landscapes and diverse cultural
traditions of the 56 regions of China, including such famous
historical sites as the "Peking Man," the Great Wall and the
Imperial Palace of the Ming and Qing dynasties. 
</P>
