<BODY>
<HEADLINE> U.S. Decision Not to Deploy NMD Is Rational: Spokesman </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 2 (Xinhua) -- China said today that U.S.
Bill Clinton's decision not to deploy the National Missile Defense
(NMD) is "rational".
</P>
<P>
Chinese Foreign Ministry spokesman Zhu Bangzao, in a statement
on the matter, said that China has taken note of such a decision
made by President Clinton on September 1, and held that the
decision is rational.
</P>
<P>
China reiterates that the maintenance of the global strategic
stability and security is in the interests of all countries, and
conducive to world peace and stability as well as to international
arms control and disarmament efforts, he said.
</P>
<P>
"We hope that the U.S. government will have more contact and
discussions with other countries on the matter, so as to make a
decision which could serve the interests of countries and peoples
all over the world," he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
