<HEADLINE> Yugoslavia Condemns U.S. Violation of U.N. Norm </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, September 1 (Xinhua) -- The Yugoslav Foreign Ministry
issued a statement Friday accusing the United States of barring
its parliamentary delegation from attending the first global
gathering of parliamentary leaders.
</P>
<P>
The statement said the U.S. government refused to grant visas
to the Yugoslav parliamentary delegation, regardless of the Inter-
Parliamentary Union's formal invitation to the Yugoslav parliament.
</P>
<P>
The statement said the action violated the union's principle
and also failed to keep its promise of granting visas to all
participating countries equally.
</P>
<P>
The visa refusal shows that the U.S. government continues its
hegemonism policies and tramples on international law and the rule
of international relationships, the statement said.
</P>
<P>
The three-day millennium meeting of parliamentary leaders
opened at the United Nations headquarters in New York Wednesday
with the participation of 156 parliamentary leaders from 142
countries. 
</P>
