<HEADLINE> Japanese Team Sales Peak K-2 of Karakoram Range </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, September 1 (Xinhua) -- A five-member expedition
from Japan has conquered the world's second highest mountain peak,
K-2, The Associated Press of Pakistan reported quoting delayed
reports available here Friday.
</P>
<P>
The team leader to the 8,611 meters high K-2, situated in the
Karakoram range, was named as Reiko Terasawa.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, a four-member French expedition, led by Nicolas
Sieger, has scaled the 7,010 meters high "Unnamed" peak in the
Northern Areas of Pakistan.
</P>
<P>
Nicolas Sieger himself was the only member of the team to make
it to the top of the mountain. 
</P>
