<HEADLINE> Highlights of Major Beijing-Based Newspapers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 2 (Xinhua) -- The following is the
highlights of today's major Beijing-based newspapers:
</P>
<P>
All the newspapers report on the frontpage that China
successfully put its earth survey satellite, the ZY-2, into orbit
with a Chinese Long March 4-B rocket that blasted off Friday
morning from the Taiyuan Launch Center in north China's Shanxi
Province.
</P>
<P>
The satellite, designed to gather and transmit remote sensing
image and data, can be used for territorial surveys, city planning,
crop yield assessments and disaster monitoring, as well as
scientific experiments.
</P>
<P>
Most of the newspapers also carried a report urging all
members of the Communist Party of China (CPC), especially leading
officials, to implement important instructions on Party building
by CPC General Secretary Jiang Zemin.
</P>
<P>
 People's Daily
</P>
<P>
-- Northwestern China's Jiuquan Iron and Steel (Group) Company
has scored great business success thanks to its importance
attached to production, reform and workers. In the first six
months of this year, the company realized 1.25 billion yuan in
total industrial output value, 2.16 billion yuan in sales earnings
and 415 million yuan in pre-tax profits, all showing double-digit
increases from the same period last year. Its total assets has
risen to 11.64 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
-- China has made tremendous progress in revamping state-owned
enterprises (SOE) since the beginning of the year. From January to
June, state-owned and state-controled industrial enterprises
created 90.3 billion yuan in combined profits, triple the figure
of last year.
</P>
<P>
The number of money-losing large and medium-sized state-owned
and state-controled industrial enterprises has decreased from 6,
599 in 1997 to 3,626 by June this year.
</P>
<P>
Xinhua Daily Telegraph
</P>
<P>
-- Wuyishan City of east China's Fujian Province has realized
an average growth rate of 12.42 percent in gross domestic product
(GDP) and 18.27 percent in its revenue in the past two decade.
</P>
<P>
-- Beijing is fully bracing up for efforts to win a bid in
hosting the Olympics Games in the year of 2008.
</P>
<P>
 China Daily
</P>
<P>
-- China is preparing to adopt a quota system to promote the
use of energy from renewable sources in the next Five-Year Plan (
2001-2005), according to an official with the State Development
Planning Commission.
</P>
<P>
-- Protecting the environment while developing the economy will
be a top priority for Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region, said
Ablait Abdureshit, the regional chairman, at the 2000 Urumqi
Economic and Trade Fair that opened Friday.
</P>
<P>
-- Air pollution in China's key cities will be targeted under a
new amended law which took effect Friday, a top official said.
</P>
</TEXT>
