<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Romania Faces Setback in Agricultural Production </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, September 1 (Xinhua) -- Farm production will face a
setback this year, said Romanian Prime Minister Mugur Isarescu
here Friday.
</P>
<P>
"This will seriously influence the fulfillment of national
economic growth goals," he said.
</P>
<P>
Romania this year is suffering the worst drought in a century.
"This has caused a 20 percent decrease in farm production, or a
loss of 500 million U.S. dollars, or possibly even 1 billion
dollars compared with an average bumper harvest year," said the
Romanian leader.
</P>
<P>
Agricultural production counts for 15 percent of Romania's
gross domestic product (GDP).
</P>
<P>
The reduction of agricultural production will result in a drop
of 3 percentage points in the GDP, said Constantin Chirca, vice
chairman of the State Statistical Commission of Romania. "But
industrial growth in the year will make up for the loss," he added.
</P>
<P>
In a bid to end a drop in the national economy occurring over
the past three years, Romania's GDP growth rate for the year 2000
has been set at 1.3 percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
