<HEADLINE> Dominica Hopes to Boost Economic Ties With Central America, Caribbean </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, September 1 (Xinhua) -- Dominican President
Hipolito Mejia said Friday that his country is planning to improve
economic ties with countries in the Central American and Caribbean
region, according to a report from Santo Domingo, capital of
Dominica.
</P>
<P>
The export of Dominica goods to the Central American and
Caribbean region accounts for a small portion in its total sales
abroad in 1999 which amounted to 5.203 billion U.S. dollars, Mejia
said at the annual meeting of the Caribbean Society of Food
Cultivation (CSFC).
</P>
<P>
The Caribbean islands market must be "tied up" for the products
of Dominica, Mejia added.
</P>
<P>
The government of Dominica has a special interest in increasing
its export volume to the Caribbean, said sources from the
Dominican Center for the Promotion of Exports.
</P>
<P>
Prior to the closing of the CSFC meeting, the Dominican
president also ratified a plan to promote integration in Central
America and the Caribbean to raise the living standard in the area.
</P>
</TEXT>
