<HEADLINE> IDB Calls on S. America to Face Challenges </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRASILIA, September 1 (Xinhua) -- Interamerican Development
Bank (IDB) Chairman Enrique Iglesias called on the South American
countries Friday to surmount all the pending challenges to achieve
the regional integration.
</P>
<P>
Iglesias suggested at the on-going South American summit that
the countries concerned arrive at clear and transparent agreements
for attraction of long-term investment and improvement of South
American exports.
</P>
<P>
Iglesias identified the challenges as regulation of
infrastructure services, maintenance of macroeconomic policies,
reduction of risks to private enterprises interested in
infrastructure, and wider cooperation in services improvement.
</P>
</TEXT>
