<BODY>
<HEADLINE> S. American Summit Asks For Fair Basis for FTAA Talks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRASILIA, September 1 (Xinhua) -- South American presidents
stressed here Friday that talks on creation of the Free Trade Area
of the Americas (FTAA) must be conducted on fair and balanced
bases that will assure effective access to markets for their
countries' products.
</P>
<P>
The 12 South American presidents, who were here for a two-day
summit meeting that ended Friday, reaffirmed in the "Communique of
Brasilia" their commitment to the "progressive construction" of
the FTAA.
</P>
<P>
They said the FTAA negotiations must take into consideration
the differences in the levels of development and the size of the
economies of the participating countries.
</P>
<P>
"The hemispheric project must be an effective instrument for
the sustainable and fair development of all the American countries,
" says the communique.
</P>
<P>
The South American presidents also decided to intensify
coordination of negotiating positions in the talks related to the
FTAA, said the communique. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
