<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Venezuelan Oil Price Up to 30.40 Dollars </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CARACAS, September 1 (Xinhua) -- The average price for the
Venezuelan oil for exports went up to 30.40 dollars per barrel
during the period of August 28 to September 1, registering a 1.72
dollar increase over the average price for the previous week.
</P>
<P>
The Mines and Energy Ministry said Friday that the Organization
of Petroleum Exporting Countries (OPEC) basket average price was
31.96 dollars per barrel, and the price of the Brent oil went up
to 34.25 dollar, 2.01 and 3.34 dollars above the prices of the
previous week, respectively.
</P>
<P>
The average price was quoted in August of the year 2000 at 27.
41 dollars per barrel.  
</P>
