<HEADLINE> Chilean, Bolivian Presidents Meet in Brasilia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRASILIA, September 1 (Xinhua) -- Chilean President Ricardo
Lagos and his Bolivian counterpart Hugo Banzer met Friday in
Brasilia on the sideline of the first South American Summit.
</P>
<P>
The two leaders discussed negotiations on the road project
designed to link Bolivia, Brazil, Paraguay and Chile.
</P>
<P>
Lagos said that the presidents of the four countries will
commit themselves to a new round of negotiations on construction
of the road.
</P>
<P>
An infrastructure in transport, telecommunications and energy
is an important item on the agenda of the on-going South American
summit here. 
</P>
