<HEADLINE> Colombian President to Visit U.S. </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BOGOTA, September 2 (Xinhua) -- Colombian President Andres
Pastrana and Finance Minister Juan Manuel Santos will visit the
United States from next Tuesday to Friday, local press reported
Saturday.
</P>
<P>
They will try to convince international investors that the
Colombian economy is sound and they will also seek support for a 1.
8 billion dollar credit for the next year.
</P>
<P>
On Tuesday, Santos will meet with U.S. Treasury Secretary Larry
Summers to ask support for an operation the Colombian government
plans to carry out for 1.8 billion dollars for next year budget.
</P>
<P>
The Colombian finance minister will also meet with
International Monetary Fund (IMF) and World Bank executives to
brief them on the performance of the Colombian economy during the
first half of 2000 and the budgetary adjustment measures that have
been taken.
</P>
<P>
He said that the IMF board of directors will meet September 7
to evaluate the compliance with the commitments agreed between the
Colombian government and the IMF.
</P>
<P>
President Pastrana and Santos will meet with investors and
representatives of risk evaluation firms to explain the medium-
and long-term plans the Pastrana administration has adopted.
</P>
</TEXT>
