<HEADLINE> Fifty Colombian Rebels Killed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BOGOTA, September 2 (Xinhua) -- Colombian Defense Minister Luis
Fernando Ramirez said Saturday that at least 50 guerrillas of the
Revolutionary Armed Forces of Colombia (FARC) have been killed in
the fighting in the western mountains of the Risaralda department.
15 members of the armed forces were also killed.
</P>
<P>
Ramirez made the announcement in Pereira (the Risaralda capital)
, where he went with President Andres Pastrana, to overfly the
region where the fighting has been going on since Thursday.
</P>
<P>
A colonel and seven soldiers were killed in an ambush and in
the attack against the FARC, and seven more died early Saturday
when a military aircraft that was supporting the troops on the
ground crashed against a mountain.  
</P>
</TEXT>
