<DOCNO> XIE20000902.0156 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-09-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Prodi Hopes Euro Has "Moment of Glory" </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, September 2 (Xinhua) -- The euro will have its "moment of
glory," despite its recent struggles against the dollar, European
Commission President Romano Prodi asserted Saturday.
</P>
<P>
He added that it was important for "institutions to function"
and that the euro's value would follow.
</P>
<P>
Speaking before the prestigious Ambrosetti conference in
Italian northern city of Cernobbio, Prodi declared himself "
tranquil" in the face of the euro's weak standing against the
dollar, which hovered mostly between 88 and 90 cents this week.
</P>
<P>
Prodi added that "the economy itself must show itself to be
strong like America's."
</P>
<P>
Asked whether the euro needed help in the form of stronger
monetary policy, Prodi said that was the "great problem facing the
Europe of the future: how to adjust decision-making to the new
reality."
</P>
<P>
Speaking of the EU's future, Prodi said that expanding the
European Union eastward will result in "economic success for
everyone," despite the tendency of many to view enlargement as a "
danger".
</P>
<P>
Prodi insisted that expanding the group of 15 nations,
especially to include former Soviet-block nations, will be done "
in a way that reinforces and does not weaken the economy."
</P>
</TEXT>
