<DOCNO> XIE20000902.0157 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-09-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Neo-Nazis Protest Against Globalization in Italy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, September 2 (Xinhua) -- About 400 neo-Nazis from northern
Italy and Germany marched to a top international think-tank
meeting which held in Cernobbio of Northern Italy Saturday,
chanting slogans against globalization and in favor of economic
and monetary sovereignty.
</P>
<P>
Dressed mostly in black shirts and carrying traditional neo-
Fascist symbols like the Celtic cross, they blocked the main road
to Villa D'Este, site of the prestigious Cernobbio financial and
geo-political symposium.
</P>
<P>
Luminaries like Italian economic patriarch Gianni Agnelli,
Premier Giuliano Amato, European Central Bank President Wim
Duisenberg and European Commission President Romano Prodi were
inside at the time.
</P>
<P>
Carrying placards like "national rebellion to globalization", "
we're together for history, you for power" and "we're against your
American imperialism," the far-rightists were mostly from Italy's
northern region of Lombardy and Veneto, but also some from Germany.
</P>
</TEXT>
